description:
A fictional history of the future for the curious. Written in the waning days of the Cold War, so there will be some inaccurate prognostications from today's perspective but a good read nevertheless...


From Wikipedia:

&quot;The Third Millennium: A History of the World AD 2000-3000 is a 1985 book written by Brian Stableford and David Langford. It is a fictional historical account, from the perspective of the year 3000, giving a future history of humanity and its technological and sociological developments.&quot;


If you like this kind of material, you might also want to check out the &quot;Terran Trade Authority&quot; book series by Stewart Cowley:
 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://thepiratebay.se/search/stewart%20cowley/0/7/0&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://thepiratebay.se/search/stewart%20cowley/0/7/0&lt;/a&gt;

Both are futuristic &quot;histories&quot; of mankind, the main difference being that &quot;The Third Millennium&quot; has an Earth-centered perspective while the &quot;Terran Trade Authority&quot; series takes a slightly more imaginative space-centered perspective
